# cardio-risk-rf

Production-grade tabular cardiovascular-risk classifier on the Framingham Heart Study (4240 patients, 10-year CHD). Main artefact is `cardio_risk_lgbm.joblib` (LightGBM + SHAP); baseline `cardio_risk_rf.joblib` (RandomForest + median imputer).

## Metrics (held-out test, n={{ test_size }})

{{ metrics_table }}

## Usage

```python
from huggingface_hub import hf_hub_download
import joblib, pandas as pd

path = hf_hub_download(repo_id="{{ repo_id }}", filename="cardio_risk_lgbm.joblib")
model = joblib.load(path)
x = pd.DataFrame([{{ widget_payload }}])
print(model.predict_proba(x))
```

## Feature order (16)

`male, age, education, currentSmoker, cigsPerDay, BPMeds, prevalentStroke, prevalentHyp, diabetes, totChol, sysBP, diaBP, BMI, heartRate, glucose`.
Any field may be `null`; LightGBM handles NaN natively, RandomForest pipeline imputes with the training-set median.

## Intended use

Educational artifact. Not a medical device. Do not use for clinical decisions.
